GameWindow - Class in game_main
The class GameWindow is the main class of this component.User of this component can extend this class and get game screen with game loop.The game loop is provided by MainThread class.User must implement 3 abstract methods of this class to make his game.The GameWindow.load(),GameWindow.update() and GameWindow.draw() method.

M

MainThread - Class in game_main
The MainThread class working in background and allows dynamic in the game.The main function of this class is to call GameWindow.update() and GameWindow.draw() method multiple times in second MainThread.targetTime.This class is vital for game because game must always be interactive and dynamic.
MainThread(GameWindow) - Constructor for class game_main.MainThread
Class constructor
Map - Class in map_editor
The function of Map class is to fill screen background with smaller images and set positions of game objects.To use this class user must fill its matrix(Map.map,Map.spriteList and Map.backgraundImages.The value before # at matrix[y][x] is the index of image in Map.backgraundImages which will be draw at position(x*filedWidth,y*filedHeight).The value after is the index of Sprite2D in Map.spriteList which move to position(x*filedWidth,y*filedHeight).
Map(int, int, int, int) - Constructor for class map_editor.Map
Class constructor

P

Player - Class in game_main
This class represent the game object in player control.It contains Sprite2D,control buttons and other necessarily parameters.It has integrated functionality to move in all directions, user only need to select button for each direction.The position is represent with Vector2.Component x of vector is x coordinate of player and component y is y coordinate of player.

PositionStrategy - Class in map_editor
The PositionStrategy is the simplest implementation of MapRenderStrategy.This strategy only draw map fields at position(x*filedWidth,y*filedHeight) without any scaling and other image transformations.

ScaleStrategy - Class in map_editor
The ScaleStrategy is the implementation of MapRenderStrategy.This strategy scale all background images(Map.getBackgraundImages()) and sprites(Map.getSpriteList()) before drawing.After scaling size of all images and sprites will be equal to map field size.
